### Gregorian calendar months and years {#sec-gregm}

`Decalendar` only uses months for converting to and from Gregorian calendar dates. Nevertheless, discussing months can help to explain how `Decalendar` works. The `Decalendar` year ends with January and February, as shown in @tbl-gregm. During these two months, the `Decalendar` year is 1 less than the Gregorian calendar year. To obtain a `Decalendar` year (`dy`) from a Gregorian calendar year (`gy`) and month number (`gm`), we subtract 1 from `gy` if `gm` is less than 3 ($dy = gy - [gm < 3]$). To obtain a Gregorian calendar year (`gy`) from a `Decalendar` year (`dy`) and `doty`, we add 1 to `dy` if `doty` is greater than 305 ($gy = dy + [dm > 305]$). Code to convert between `Decalendar` and Gregorian calendar years is provided in @exm-gregm.

