### Leap years {#sec-transl}

In leap years, `Dek` `36` contains the last 6 days of the current year and the first 4 days of the subsequent year. Interestingly, `Dek` `36` always contain 6 workdays and 4 restdays, just like every other `dek`, but in leaps years these days do not follow the typical order of `Schedule` `3`. Leap years end in 3 restdays instead of 2, because Leap Day (`Day` `365`) is always a holiday. Leap day is always a `Penday` and always followed by a `Nulday`. After Leap Day, the normal rhythm of `Schedule` `3` resumes. @tbl-leap shows the positive and negative `doties` of the days in `Dek` `36` in leap years, as well as their names and their types (work or rest).

